2.1.12 The "Any" type
---------------------

It is not really possible for an object to be of "Any" type, but it is
nevertheless a valid type value.  It gets used in certain (rather rare)
circumstances, e.g. `as.vector(x, "any")', indicating that type coercion
should not be done.


