10.2 Comments
=============

Comments in R are ignored by the parser.  Any text from a `#' character
to the end of the line is taken to be a comment, unless the `#'
character is inside a quoted string. For example,

     > x <- 1  # This is a comment...
     > y <- "  #... but this is not."


